  "text": "The Kubernetes service account token auto-mounting system involves three main components:\n\n## 1. Admission Controller — Token Injection\n**File:** `plugin/pkg/admission/serviceaccount/admission.go`\n\nThis is the core admission plugin (`Plugin` struct, registered as `ServiceAccount`) that intercepts Pod CREATE requests. Key functions:\n- `Admit()`: The mutating admission handler. Sets the default service account name (`default`) if not specified, then calls `shouldAutomount()` to decide whether to inject the token, and if so calls `mountServiceAccountToken()`.\n- `shouldAutomount(sa, pod)`: Implements the precedence logic — pod-level `AutomountServiceAccountToken` wins over service account-level; defaults to `true` for backwards compatibility.\n- `mountServiceAccountToken(serviceAccount, pod)`: Injects a projected volume (via `TokenVolumeSource()`) and corresponding `VolumeMount` at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount` into every container.\n- `TokenVolumeSource()`: Returns the `ProjectedVolumeSource` containing a `ServiceAccountToken` projection, a `ConfigMap` projection for `kube-root-ca.crt`, and a `DownwardAPI` projection for the namespace.\n- `Validate()`: The validating admission handler. Enforces that mirror pods cannot reference service accounts or secrets, and optionally enforces mountable secret restrictions.\n- `MountServiceAccountToken bool` field on `Plugin`: Global flag (default `true`) that enables/disables token auto-mounting at the plugin level.\n\n## 2. Pod Spec Validation — automountServiceAccountToken Check\n**File:** `pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go`\n\nThis file contains the core API validation logic:\n- `ValidatePodSpec()`: Validates the pod specification including the `serviceAccountName` field (must be a valid service account name). The `AutomountServiceAccountToken` field on `PodSpec` is a `*bool` and is not further constrained by validation (any bool value is valid).\n- `ValidateServiceAccount()` / `ValidateServiceAccountUpdate()`: Validates service account objects. The `AutomountServiceAccountToken` field on `ServiceAccount` is similarly a `*bool` with no additional constraints.\n- The file also validates `ServiceAccountToken` projected volume sources (lines ~1164-1178), checking that `expirationSeconds` is between 10 minutes and 2^32 seconds, and that `path` is set.\n- `ValidateSecret()` (around line 6779): Validates `SecretTypeServiceAccountToken` secrets, requiring the `kubernetes.io/service-account.name` annotation.\n\n## 3. Token Controller — Secret Creation\n**File:** `pkg/controller/serviceaccount/tokens_controller.go`\n\nThe `TokensController` manages legacy `ServiceAccountToken`-type secrets:\n- `NewTokensController()`: Creates the controller, watches `ServiceAccount` and `Secret` (filtered to `SecretTypeServiceAccountToken`) informers.\n- `TokensController` struct: Holds the token generator, root CA, and work queues for service account and secret sync.\n- `syncServiceAccount()`: When a service account is deleted, calls `deleteTokens()` to remove all associated token secrets.\n- `syncSecret()`: When a token secret event occurs, ensures the service account still exists (deletes the token if not), or calls `generateTokenIfNeeded()` to populate token data.\n- `generateTokenIfNeeded()`: Populates the `token`, `ca.crt`, and `namespace` fields in a `ServiceAccountToken` secret using the configured `TokenGenerator` (JWT signer).\n- `deleteTokens()` / `deleteToken()`: Remove token secrets when service accounts are deleted.\n- `removeSecretReference()`: Removes secret references from service accounts when secrets are deleted.\n\n## Supporting Files\n- **`pkg/controller/serviceaccount/serviceaccounts_controller.go`**: `ServiceAccountsController` ensures the `default` service account exists in every namespace.\n- **`pkg/controller/serviceaccount/legacy_serviceaccount_token_cleaner.go`**: `LegacySATokenCleaner` deletes auto-generated legacy SA token secrets that have not been used for a configurable period.\n- **`pkg/controller/serviceaccount/tokengetter.go`**: `NewGetterFromClient()` provides a `ServiceAccountTokenGetter` used by the token authenticator.\n- **`cmd/kube-controller-manager/app/core.go`**: Wires up `startServiceAccountTokenController` and `startLegacyServiceAccountTokenCleanerController` in the controller manager.\n\n## Data Flow\n1. A Pod is created → `ServiceAccount` admission plugin `Admit()` is called.\n2. `shouldAutomount()` checks `pod.Spec.AutomountServiceAccountToken` (pod wins) then `sa.AutomountServiceAccountToken` (SA-level), defaulting to `true`.\n3. If automounting is enabled, `mountServiceAccountToken()` injects a projected volume with a bound service account token, CA cert, and namespace into the pod spec.\n4. Separately, the `TokensController` watches for `ServiceAccountToken`-type secrets and calls `generateTokenIfNeeded()` to sign and populate legacy token secrets (for older clients that request them explicitly).\n5. `ValidatePodSpec()` in `pkg/apis/core/validation/validation.go` validates the `serviceAccountName` field and projected `ServiceAccountToken` volume parameters."
